title: Death Due To Self Inflicted Gun Shot Wound
content:
Sullivan County, Ind (WIBQ) - More details have been released in the death of a Sullivan County teen.
Investigators say that 14 year old Jacob Setter died of a self inflicted gun shot wound this past Sunday around Noon.
Police have not said if the shooting was accidental or intentional or if there were any witnesses.
The incident happened in the woods behind Setter’s home in Graysville.
